-- Canada Stocks Rise, Erasing Loss, as Barrick, Research In Motion Advance
-- Stephen Kleege
-- 2010-06-23T18:39:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-23/canada-stocks-rise-erasing-loss-as-barrick-research-in-motion-advance.html

          
          
             Canada’s main stock index rose,
erasing an earlier loss, as Barrick Gold Corp. and Research In
Motion gained.  
 The Standard & Poor’s/TSX Composite Index advanced 24.45
points, or 0.2 percent, to 11,822.39 at 2:46 p.m. in Toronto,
after falling as much as 0.6 percent.  
 Barrick climbed 1 percent to C$46.48, while RIM rallied 3.3
percent to C$62.43.  
          
          


  


        